1. Dependencies (caffe.berkeleyvision.org/install_apt.html)
	sudo apt-get install libprotobuf-dev libleveldb-dev libsnappy-dev libopencv-dev libhdf5-serial-dev protobuf-compiler
	sudo apt-get install --no-install-recommends libboost-all-dev
	sudo apt-get install libatlas-base-dev
	sudo apt-get install python-dev python3-dev
	sudo apt-get install libgflags-dev libgoogle-glog-dev liblmdb-dev

2.CUDA (developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads)
	2.1 Download Network installer (.deb)
	2.2 Follow instructions in Section 3.6 from here (developer.download.nvidia.com/compute/cuda/7_0/Prod/doc/CUDA_Getting_Started_Linux.pdf):
		sudo dpkg -i cuda-repo-<distro>_<version>_<architecture>.deb
		sudo apt-get update
		sudo apt-get install cuda
export PATH=/usr/local/cuda-7.0/bin:$PATH$
 		export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/cuda-7.0/lib64:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH

3. GPU drivers (only when CUDA did not install the latest)
	sudo apt-get update
	In Additional drivers select the recommended NVIDIA driver*


4. (Opt) Install cuDNN (developer.nvidia.com/cudnn)
	To compile with cuDNN set the USE_CUDNN := 1 flag set in your Makefile.config.

5. Prepare compilation (caffe.berkeleyvision.org/installation.html)
	git clone https://github.com/BVLC/caffe.git
	cd caffe
	cp Makefile.config.example Makefile.config
	Adjust makefile
		Uncomment USE_CUDNN := 1
		Change python version: 'PYTHON_INCLUDE := /usr/include/python3.4'
6. Compile**
	make all
	make test
	make pycaffe
	make runtest

7. Add caffe to PYTHONPATH
	export PYTHONPATH=/home/michael/Documents/cnn4brca/caffe/python:$PYTHONPATH


* It's not THE latest but the last pushed into the ubuntu repo (maybe 1-2 months old). For the very latest, go to nvidia.com/drivers, installing this is cumbersome (do not recommend).
** To recompile run 'make clear' first.


